  "description": "Small brown wren with a short bill. Undertail coverts warm cinnamon. Tail spiky and short. Back distinctive with darker brown blotches and white vertical streaks. Bill short with lower mandible standing out with its yellow coloration. Throat whitish, breast whitish, belly pale cinnamon. Face unpatterend.Behaviors: Skulky but it did stay in the open, mostly behind low olive twigs at the edge of a wet sedge meadow. It was interested in watching me and did a quarter circle around me.Call: loud scolding notes identifialbe as a wren but not to speciesPlumage: unknown",
